    "Mitchell G. Reddish, Nijay K. Gupta": "). [Nearness of the End] From John `[char_John_Ref]`\u2019s per-\nspective, evil was becoming so dominant in\nthe world that surely God would intervene\nsoon. In his view, the justice of God\ndemanded that wickedness not be allowed to triumph much\nlonger. By claiming that \u201cthe time is near\u201d when God would be vic-\ntorious over evil, John `[char_John_Ref]` offered his readers hope and encouragement.\nThey must persevere only a short while longer.\nWhat were these events that \u201cmust soon take place\u201d? As his work\nmakes clear, John `[char_John_Ref]` expected the destruction of Rome to be one of\nthe components of the final events of history. The Roman emper-\nors, with their claims to divine status, were a part of the forces of\nevil that would soon be defeated. These and other events that\nv. 3)\n\u2022 Woman is devoured by the beast (\nv. 3)\n\u2022 Seated on many waters (\n3. Laments over the City\u201418:9-19\na. Laments by the Kings\u201418:9-10\nb. Laments by the Merchants\u201418:11-17a\nc. Laments by the Mariners\u201418:17b-19",
    "John Trapp": "Into the wilderness ] Whither the true Church fled, Re. xii., of which they must be (saith one) that can learn to know the Romish Church to be a whore, condemned of God. I saw a woman ] { See Trapp on \"Re 17:1\" } Sit upon ] Not going afoot, as Christ and the apostles did, but magnificently mounted, as the pope is ever, either upon a stately palfrey (emperors holding his stirrup) or upon men\u2019s shoulders. England was once called the pope\u2019s ass, for bearing his intolerable exactions. This ass he held by the ears instead of a bridle. Upon a scarlet coloured beast ] The proper colour of the court of Rome; and it well serves to set forth their pomp and their hypocrisy. Innocent IV gave a red hat to his cardinals, to show them (as he said) that they should be ready to shed their blood for the truth. But that painter was nearer the point, who being blamed by a cardinal for colouring the visages of Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` and Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]` too red, tartly replied, that he painted them so as blushing at the stateliness and sinfulness of his successors. Full of names of blasphemy ] His head only before was busked with the blasphemy, #Re 13:1 , now his whole body. Thus evil men and seducers grow worse and worse, deceiving and being deceived, #2Ti 3:13 .\nVer.\n3. Into the wilderness] Whither the true Church fled, Re. xii., of which they must be (saith one) that can learn to know the Romish Church to be a whore, condemned of God. [v_Rev_17_1] I saw a woman] {See Trapp on \"Re 17:1\"} Sit upon] Not going afoot, as Christ and the apostles did, but magnificently mounted, as the pope is ever, either upon a stately palfrey (emperors holding his stirrup) or upon men\u2019s shoulders. England was once called the pope\u2019s ass, for bearing his intolerable exactions. This ass he held by the ears instead of a bridle. Upon a scarlet coloured beast] The proper colour of the court of Rome `[nation_Rome_Act_2]`; and it well serves to set forth their pomp and their hypocrisy. Innocent IV gave a red hat to his cardinals, to show them (as he said) that they should be ready to shed their blood for the truth. But that painter was nearer the point, who being blamed by a cardinal for colouring the visages of Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` and Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]` too red, tartly replied, that he painted them so as blushing at the stateliness and sinfulness of his successors. Full of names of blasphemy] His head only before was busked [v_Rev_13_1] with the blasphemy, #Re 13:1, now his whole body. Thus evil men and seducers grow worse and worse, deceiving and being deceived, #2Ti 3:"
