    "John Trapp": "Are ten kings ] Of ten different kingdoms, Naples, Spain, Portugal, France, Polony, Bohemia, Hungary, Denmark, Sweden, and this of England, which as it was the first of the ten that submitted to the pope\u2019s yoke, so was it the first that shook it off again in Henry VIII\u2019s time.\nVer.\n12. Are ten kings] Of ten different kingdoms, Naples, Spain, Portugal, France, Polony, Bohemia, Hungary, Denmark, Sweden, and this of England, which as it was the first of the ten that submitted to the pope\u2019s yoke, so was it the first that shook it off again in Henry VIII\u2019s time.\nVer."
